-- China Datang Starts Construction of Rooftop Solar Power Plant in Jiangsu
-- Feifei Shen
-- 2010-06-28T16:37:05Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-28/china-datang-starts-construction-of-rooftop-solar-power-plant-in-jiangsu.html

          
          
                  June 28 (Bloomberg New Energy Finance) --  China Datang
Corp.,  the nationâ€™s second-largest power producer, has started
construction of a 5.8 megawatt rooftop solar plant in Jiangsu
province, the Xinhua state news agency reported.  
 The 160 million-yuan ($24 million) project in Wood
Industrial Park in Dafeng port is scheduled to be commissioned
by November. It is the first phase of a 10-megawatt, 350
million-yuan plant, according to Xinhua.  
 The project is expected to generate 6.2 gigawatt hours of
power and reduce 5,128 tons of carbon emissions. China Datang
Renewable Power, a subsidiary of Datang, recently secured
approval from the National Energy Administration for an initial
public share offering in Hong Kong.  
